abstract: We don’t know the full impact on 2020 yet, but here’s what we’re looking for.

lead_paragraph: Hi. Welcome to On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Lisa Lerer, your host, back from vacation just in time for a big day in Washington.

abstract: The president’s eldest son is using a newfound platform as an author to recast the story of the 2016 election — and every political battle that came after.
snippet: The president’s eldest son is using a newfound platform as an author to recast the story of the 2016 election — and every political battle that came after.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On the eve of the first public hearing in the Democratic-led impeachment against President Trump, his eldest son was standing in the lobby of the family hotel, delivering firm handshakes and turning over copies of his book, “Triggered: How the Left Thrives on Hate and Wants to Silence Us,” to supporters who had paid $32 for the experience.

abstract: As leading Democrats fight for ballot access, voting rights and diverse representation, their marquee presidential contest is hard to participate in and takes place in a state that is 90 percent white.
snippet: As leading Democrats fight for ballot access, voting rights and diverse representation, their marquee presidential contest is hard to participate in and takes place in a state that is 90 percent white.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Even the Democrats trying to win the Iowa caucuses won’t defend them.

abstract: SoftBank poured money into start-ups that use armies of contractors. That has upended the lives of drivers, hotel operators and real estate agents around the world.
snippet: SoftBank poured money into start-ups that use armies of contractors. That has upended the lives of drivers, hotel operators and real estate agents around the world.
lead_paragraph: For five years, Sunil Solankey, a retired captain in the Indian Army, had run the 20-room Four Sight Hotel in a New Delhi suburb. Business was steady, but he longed to make the establishment a destination for lucrative business travelers.

abstract: The autonomous region of Finland offers secluded lodgings, fresh seafood and miles of serene coastline to explore.
snippet: The autonomous region of Finland offers secluded lodgings, fresh seafood and miles of serene coastline to explore.
lead_paragraph: Situated 25 miles east of the Swedish coast, and officially an autonomous region of southwestern Finland, the Aland archipelago consists of about 6,700 named islands and 20,000 smaller rocky outcrops and islets waiting to be discovered. Conquered by Russia in the early 19th century, Aland was declared a Finnish territory in 1921, but the core of its traditions are Swedish, as is the official language. With the Baltic Sea as its backdrop, the archipelago ranges topographically from barren coastal cliffs to stunning white-sand beaches to forests and fertile farmland. Only 35 of the Aland Islands are inhabited and easily accessible from mainland Sweden and Finland; the central islands are linked to one another by bridges and cable ferries, while car ferries connect the archipelago’s more remote reaches.

abstract: Michael Bloomberg has filed paperwork in two states, while Deval Patrick is expected to announce his intentions soon.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg has filed paperwork in two states, while Deval Patrick is expected to announce his intentions soon.
lead_paragraph: It was late summer and the Democratic presidential primary was in flux. Joseph R. Biden Jr. was sinking in national polls and Senator Elizabeth Warren was on the rise. And two men, Michael R. Bloomberg and Deval Patrick, were again thinking quietly about running for president.
